-- China's Stocks Extend Monthly Rally as Consumer, Technology Shares Climb
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-25T03:04:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/china-s-stocks-extend-monthly-rally-as-consumer-technology-shares-climb.html
China’s stocks rose for the first
time in three days on the prospect the country’s next five-year
economic plan will boost consumer and technology companies,
while the yuan’s gain added to speculation of more fund inflows.  The Shanghai Composite Index advanced 0.6 percent to
2,993.81 at 11:03 a.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  